# Novy Mir, Miyakinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Novy Mir () is a rural locality (a village) in Miyakibashevsky Selsoviet, Miyakinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 304 as of 2010. There are 6 streets.
Geography
Novy Mir is located 24&nbsp;km northeast of Kirgiz-Miyaki (the district's administrative centre) by road. Nikolayevka is the nearest rural locality.
